The firewood is burning with a crackling sound.[l][r]
The temperature in high mountains is low even in summer.
And this natural warmth was very comforting. [l][r]
[r]"But whatever the form, it's good to be able to gather together like this again." [l][r]
"Yes, indeed." [l][r]
With that, Kanazawa accepts the coffee his wife gave him and takes a sip. [l][r]
[r]This is a camp where you can see the stars somewhere in Nagano Prefecture[r]
Place. [r]
When we looked up at the sky, a sky full of stars was looking down on us.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
It's been several months since Yuri was found. She still hasn't woken up. [l]Honestly, it was painful to see and hear Chito's reaction when she first saw Yuri in a coma. [l][r]
All I could do was close the door quietly so that her sobs wouldn't reach the outside. [l][r]

[r]"Chito is a really amazing girl. Even though all the hard work she put in was wasted, she never gave up." [l][r]
[r]As I took a sip of the coffee and savored its aroma, I remembered those times.
[l][r]
It was some time after leaving Chito and Yuri alone. [l][r]

[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[bg  time="1000"  method="crossfade"  storage="curtain.jpg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
When she returned to check on them, she had tear stains on her face, but her expression was full of determination.[l][r]
[r]Ah, those were the eyes I had seen so many times; the eyes of a girl brazenly challenging despair.
[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
[r]"Ishii. I've decided." [l][r]
"...What?" [l][r]
"I'll stay by Yu's side as much as I can. I'll be waiting so that he'll wake up whenever he wants." [l][r]
"...I see. [l]That's right, why don't you try it?" [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[bg  time="1000"  method="crossfade"  storage="hospital7.jpg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
So Chito began to visit Yuri whenever she had time.[l][r]
She would talk about what had happened that day until the very last minute of visiting hours, study, and sometimes even stay in the hospital room in turns with Yuri's parents. Whenever she found time, she would pour it all into Yuri.[l][r]
[r] I was worried that he might end up damaging his health, so I told him to take a few days off. [l][r]
However, Chito's health deteriorates if she is away from Yuri for a long time, and she feels much better when she comes to Yuri's hospital room.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
According to Chito, working hard for Yuri was also good for her, so it wasn't hard for her at all.[l][r]
[r]And so a month... half a year... and the days passed. [l][r]
Even though Chito tried hard to visit Yuri, he still didn't seem to be waking up. [l][r]
Even so, Chito never gave up and continued to visit Yuri.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[bg  time="1500"  method="crossfade"  storage="campb.jpg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"'I'm always with Yuri, so it's okay.'
… Tito said so clearly. [l][r]
Perhaps something was born within that child, or he woke up, or he realized something." [l][r]

[_tb_end_text]

[bg  time="1500"  method="crossfade"  storage="yamahosi.jpg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
[r] Now, Chito and Yuri are going to a nearby grassland to watch the stars. [l][r]
I was a little worried about whether it would be okay for the two of us to be alone, but it wasn't too far away and the campsite was well-maintained, so as long as we were careful not to get cold, there shouldn't be any problems. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"I don't think there are many kids who have such a strong bond. I'm envious." [l][r]
When Kanazawa said that, the lady next to him looked a little annoyed. I didn't miss it, but I wasn't rude enough to point it out. [l]Now, Kanazawa-kun, you have to do your best to follow up. [l][r]
[r] "It's just a baseless prediction.
But..." I muttered, lowering my eyes slightly. [l][r]

I put my coffee down and recalled Chito's despair-defying eyes and Yuri's positive attitude. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"...I think Yuri will really wake up soon.
"Yo." [l][r]
[r]"You're making wild theories like Tito." [l][r]
"I felt like I somehow understood how she felt." [l][r]
[r]I laughed at myself. But the Kanazawas gave me a smile that seemed to include understanding. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"I feel the same way, though." [l][r]
That may be so. For some reason, I don't feel like there's a painful future ahead. [l] Even if Yuri hadn't woken up, I think we'd still be the same as always. [l][r]
[r]Well, this feeling is similar to what you feel when a plane wing breaks.[l][r]
No... or maybe it's a little different. It was a strange feeling. [l][r]
[r]Well, that's fine. [l][r]
[r]I guess I just need to help them as much as I can so that they can live their lives in a positive way. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

